Foot & mouth disease - Zimbabwe 19990827.1504
Date: Tuesday, August 21, 2001 8:27 AM
From: Michael Meredith <meredith@farmline.com>
Source: Reuters [edited

Zimbabwe suspends beef exports over foot and mouth disease
----------------------------------------------------------
HARARE - Zimbabwe Agriculture Permanent Secretary Ngoni Masoka [is reported
to have said that the country has suspended beef exports after an outbreak
of foot and mouth disease at a feedlot of the state-owned beef corporation
near the second city of Bulawayo, in the mainly ranching province of
Matabeleland. He said, "The Department of Veterinary Services has reported,
from clinical observations, an outbreak of foot and mouth disease within
the Cold Storage Company's Willsgrove Feedlot, to the east of Bulawayo."
The government [is said to have taken steps to isolate and eradicate the
disease, including restricting cattle movement and large-scale farm
inspections, [and has temporarily stopped all beef exports.
More news is available at: <http://www.pighealth.com/diseases/FMD/news.htm>
